-- Passera Sold Shares in Intesa, Former CEO Writes in Corriere
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2011-12-31T13:35:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-31/passera-sold-shares-in-intesa-former-ceo-writes-in-corriere.html
Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP) ’s former Chief
Executive Officer  Corrado Passera  sold all his shares in the
Italian bank in recent days, he wrote in a letter published in
Corriere della Sera.  Passera, now Italian Economic Development Minister, said he
didn’t have any conflicts of interest after selling the shares,
which he wasn’t obliged to do.  To contact the reporter on this story:
